title: Kyung Wha Chung - Mendelssohn & Elgar Violin Concertos
description:
On this CD:

1. Concerto for Violin and Orchestra in E minor
Composed by Felix Mendelssohn
Performed by Montreal Symphony Orchestra
with Kyung-Wha Chung
Conducted by Charles Dutoit

2. Concerto for Violin and Orchestra in B minor
Composed by Sir Edward Elgar
Performed by London Philharmonic Orchestra
with Kyung-Wha Chung
Conducted by Sir Georg Solti


EAC + flac, log, cue, m3u, full scans
